<Author>anyone
<Content>Very Dated - Very Expensive - Not 5 star! At $700 a night including taxes including a resort charge for sunbeds! including breakfast I think this hotel should be a lot higher standard!The hotel public areas are superb - having enjoyed a drink here last year we decided to stay overnight before joinng Sea Dream Yacht Club in San Juan - the room are very tired and not 5 star - the service also isnt 5 star - this is a very very very busy transient hotel similar to the Jumeirah Beach hotel type of busy busy hotel - not an exclusive Ritz Carlton property - there are just far too many people everywhere in a very overcrowded pool area and all the bar areas are full - breakfast is not a pleasant refinded experience as everywhere is so very very busyThe rooms themselves are in urgent need of a major upgrade and refurb as charging $700 per night should leave plenty of money to spend on getting the standard higherThe public areas are nice and very rtitz carlton elegant at first glance - although the bar area is still very small for the size of the hotel and the live music at night in the bar area is so loud that you cannot enjoy a conversation - again not the usual refined Ritz Carlton style we are used toLanguage is a problem with the service as the staff often didnt understand basic requests - our turn down service was completely missed which is poor at $700 per night and when I requested it at 11pm having got back to the room not done they did send someone over - so we had to then pay for extra drinks whilst they did the room for us and even then they didnt replace the toiletries in the bathroom or the wet robes or the bottle water - it was a very very quick turn down service after I had complained - no soft music or chocolates on the bed and not nice little extra touches that are usual at a hotel of this standardDrinks in the bar are the usual high prices which you have to accept in hotels like his - we had dinner in Il Mullino which was ok but nothing fantastic - again very expensive and very very hectic and busyBreakfast was nothing special - just an ordinary buffet and staff who didnt really understand most requests - the coffee was absolutely horrible - I enjoy a nice double espresso in the mornings but this coffee was exceptionally strong and bitterThe pathways and pool area again need refurbishing as there are lots of cracks and signs of wear - the pool area itself is quite slippy - again the property needs some money spent on itAccess to the beach is good at the back of the pool area and the beach is nice golden sand with very warm water - no lovely colours though and definitely no amazing view from the beach as all around the hotel area is very run down - no shopping within walking distance and very far from the centre of San Juan - convenient though for the airport and the aircraft noise didnt actually disturb usThe air conditioning in the room is very very old and kept cutting in during the middle of the nigh and waking us up - it was vvery noisy - not sure if this was just our room or a standard featureWe were upgraded for our $700 from a pool view room to an ocean view with a small balcony which we were glad of as I would have been even more disappointed had we been given a poor view - the balcony was tired and badly in need of a refurb and paint but there was a good view and at least we had one as there are very few rooms at this hotel that have a balconyThe bathroom was ok and had a nice large separate shower - it had been refurbished but you could see that it was basically an old style that had had a little bit of updating - all the electrics are very old not like the modern Ritz Carlton hotels and the bathroom floor was quite slippy from leaking water from the shower areaI wouldnt choose to stay here again as I think it is very overpriced for what you get but top quality hotels are hard to find in San Juan and I think this probably isstill one of the best - we will try to join our cruises from somewhere else in futureAbsolutely not up to the usual standard of Ritz Carlton Hotel and definitely not for the price - at $300 per night it would be acceptable but not at $700!! 
