<Content>My "Go To" Hotel in San Juan The Ritz Carlton is my go-to hotel whenever I find myself in San Juan in transit to another destination further down in the Caribbean. (With airline routes being cut, this is happening increasingly).In addition to the location convenient to the airport, and within walking distance of many restaurants, it's simply a great hotel. The common areas are elegant and luxurious, the service is up to par with RC standards, and the rooms are comfortable, fresh, clean. RC beds are simply luscious, and I can always count on a wonderful night's sleep. Despite the proximity to the airport, there is never any airport noise that you can hear in the rooms.The pool area is not huge, but between that and the beach, there never seems to be the unpleasant jockeying for beach loungers that one sees at other hotels (including the RC in Grand Cayman). Isla Verde's beach is nice enough, and certainly fine for a single night's stay. 
