<Content>Wonderful Honeymoon My wife and I--I am 29 and she is 26--spent our honeymoon at the Ritz, and were treated kindly and respectfully the entire stay of six days. We selected the Club Level to enjoy the various food presentations, and we were never disappointed by the food or by the concierges--all of whom were polite, knowledgeable and eager to recommend excursions, restaurants and cool lounges/clubs. Reynaldo Malave, the Club Supervisor, is an exceptional talent who assisted us nightly with suggestions and reservations. We spent most of our time between the pool and beach. We found both to be relaxing, though the breeze on the beach seemed gale force at times. The gym was more than adequate for both aerobics and weight lifting; the massages we received at the spa were superb; the on-site restaurants were impressive; the casino provided a nice distraction on one night. As a 29-year-old from Washington, D.C., I say comfortably that I know exceptional service and fine food. You'll receive both at the Ritz. And if you want a 24-hour party atmosphere, walk two blocks to the El San Juan Hotel. Just be sure to make the Ritz your base camp. 
