<Author>kimspokane
<Content>Best hotel experience to date We were at the Ritz five days prior to christmas in a concierge pool view room. Our stay at the Ritz made our subsequent christmas cruise all the more underwhelming. The most impressive part of our stay was the genuine helpful attitude of the staff. Every single staff member that we encountered during our stay made a point of saying good morning and greeting us, often by name.Our two teen daughters were attached to us for the first couple of days. One of the managers, Ramon, took us and our family on a personal tour of areas of the hotel that may be of some interest for our children to hang out. Anticipating the fact that families were traveling together for christmas they set up two large rooms for the kids and teens. One showing christmas movies with bean bag chairs, big screen tv, pop, chips, popcorn machine and an adjoing room set up with play stations, wi games, xbox all with big screen tv's. They had these rooms staffed and the staff gave the kids 1:1 time showing them how to play the games and actually playing with them. LaLa was incredible. She was able to engage our teens and even asked if we wanted her to keep them occupied for a certain amount of time so the adults could have some kid free time. This program was a no cost extra and not part of the kids program. Just one example of how the hotel went to extra lengths to ensure family holiday stays were enjoyable for kids, teens and adults and another example of how the Ritz goes a step beyond. The food was incredible and we are very picky about good food. The food and service in the concierge lounge was a perfect 10. In the afternoons the pool staff delivered complimentary fruit smoothies while we layed in the sun. Food and drinks are expensive but on par with any 4 and five star resort. The grounds are very beautiful. The beach was cleaned daily and there was pleanty of space for chairs, umbrellas, shade or sun. Plane noise was only noticed one afternoon for about 5 min at 2pm on the beach. Must have been a bunch of planes landing or taking off. You can't see them as their path must be away from the Ritz. I walked to the Marriott a ways down the beach one day just to check it out. The plane noise was very noticeable there. The ocean is not the blue blue that you see at the Ritz in St. Thomas or eagle beach in Aruba but it was just right for us and there were pleanty of people swimming. Surf lessons are offered just to the right of the ritz on the beach where the waves have a bigger break. Nightly music was offered in the lobby. Some excellent local music. The spa was not crowded and spa staff very helpful. A couple more examples of service; Our kids wanted to watch a dvd movie in the room. They could not figure out how to get the dvd player to work. My husband called for assistance. I walked into the room and thought there had been some sort of incident. Two uniformed men were in the room to show the kids and my husband how to work the dvd player. The following day one of them called us to see if we were having any further problems or needed any additional help. My daughter was horsing around in the pool and her face met the bottom of the pool causing some scrapes to her nose, forehead and lip. She was embarrassed and immediately wanted to go back to her room. A janitor saw us enter the room with her crying. He was concerned and called for help. Staff responded and two first aid people came up to fix her up and see if I wanted a doctor. Her injuries were to her ego more than face. The staff repeatedly asked me if there was anything they could do to help her feel better, ice cream... and they were genuine. She was embarrassed about being in public and so we ate dinner in the concierge lounge. Wanda went to her mother's house the next day and brought in a large fresh stalk of Aloe Vera plant. She even cut up individual peices and put in a baggie on ice for individual application. This really helped the scrapes heal fast. Even the janitor in the hall asked me how my daughter was doing. My husband usually gets a little stir crazy staying at a resort but he had an excellent relaxing time as well and we did not look forward to leaving for our cruise. The casino offers poker with a $100 buy in no limit bets. He had a lot of fun playing with the locals who were very friendly. We did not leave the resort prior to the cruise. Post cruise we stayed in old san juan which was a lot of fun. We wish we would have seen more of Puerto Rico but now have more exploring to do upon our return. Other guests during our stay were vacationing with family and extended family. It it seemed to me to be a holiday destination vacation for the majority of guests. A good majority of the children were accompanied by a nanny, or more than one attentive nannie and so unruly kids were not running around.The cost of the rooms was much higher due to christmas vacation but I feel that despite the much higher cost, the Ritz was by far the best money and value for our vacation dollar because they delivered exactly the kind of vacation we were looking for. We spent far more on the christmas cruise than we did on the concierge room stay at the Ritz and in retrospect wish we had never left the Ritz.We will definately return to Puerto Rico and stay at the Ritz. When on vacation we typically spend the extra to stay at a four or five star resort. We also typically book a suite. We opted for the concierge level room vs. a suite for this stay. I think the suites ran around 6k per night for holiday stay. Despite the fact that we did not have a balcony or suite we still had the most enjoyable tropical stay that we have had at any resort. This was due to the service. I think when we return we will stay off season when we can afford a suite. The Ritz in St. Thomas and Maui are also great. The service at the San Juan Ritz is what sets this resort apart.My daughter's face and ego have recovered. We returned home last night. We were excited to get home to our own house and beds after 24 hours in flights and airport time. The min. we walked outside the airport to 16 degree temps and snow we all quickly agreed that we wished we were still in Puerto Rico and the Ritz. In fact I'm writing this review in part as task avoidance for the 9 bags of luggage and laundry that is awaiting me in the foyer. 
