<Author>Manhattanites
<Content>Delightful Christmas stay Our family had a delightful stay at the Ritz over the Christmas holiday. We traveled with an infant and I would like to say that the amenities for a small child were excellent. We worked with the guest services manager via email prior to our stay to ensure we had a crib in the room, and it was ready for us at arrival and was in perfect condition with bedding and bumpers (although we brought our own). And you can't beat the poolside pack and plays! Great touch. The hotel overall was the perfect choice for us - just five minutes from the airport (huge plus when traveling with a baby) - with an amazing pool and easy access to a well-kept beach. There are babysitting services as well although we didn't use them. Hotel is in walking distance to a Walgreens and other stores if you need snacks, prescriptions, baby supplies or food, sunscreen, etc. The food at the resort is very good, and we are picky picky eaters! Due to the operating hours, we ate at Mares, lobby lounge and the Ocean Bar only; all were great. Room service though was our favorite - loved the seafood pasta and banana trifle so much we ordered it for three nights! Overall, service was outstanding, and we really appreciated the warm smiles and helpful attitudes even on Christmas Day when I'm sure the staff would have preferred not to be working. We have stayed at several Ritz properties over the years and this property certainly lives up to the reputation. My only suggestions (very minor) would be to put in a railing on the stepped entrance to the beach (a little slippery, especially when carrying baby), offering more local spices/coffee/artscrafts for sale in the gift shop, and expanding the hours of BLT and Il Mulino (starting dinner times of 6 pm were too hard with the baby - would have loved a 5 pm dinner or a more casual lunch option so we could try those places). We would definitely recommend this hotel for a quick stay in Puerto Rico. 
