<Author>suzieboston
<Content>Excellent, personalized service is this hotel's best asset. I stayed here with my husband for four days prior to a cruise, followed by another two days, as part of our honeymoon. Prior to the cruise, we stayed in a club level room. After that, we stayed in a regular room, so we were able to compare those experiences.Check-in. For our first check-in, we were greeted with congratulations and glasses of champagne, a very nice touch (we also came back to a bottle of champagne in the room that night). During both check-ins, we were first greeted by a bellhop who took our luggage, welcomed us warmly, and offered us bottled water. Check-in itself was easy both times. We noticed during each check-in that there were people complaining that they could not check in as early as 12:30 or 1PM. The hotel's official check-in time is 4PM, and they do try to allow early check-in when possible. I was impressed that the front desk staff handled these demanding guests professionally.Rooms: Our club level and regular rooms were identical (you don't get a better room by going with the club level). The size and decor are nothing spectacular, and not unlike those I've seen in some nice 3-star hotels (except for the Frette linens). They were clean. There was a bit of a musty odor, which is not surprising for the humid environment. The beds and pillows were very comfortable and made up nicely. Housekeeping comes twice a day (in the evening this included turn-down, replenishing towels and straightening up the room). The TV is a flat screen. There were, robes, plenty of Bulgari toiletries, and a good hair dryer in the bathroom. Service: The service throughout the hotel was fantastic. The rooms at this hotel aren't all that special, but the service is 5-star. You will often be greeted by name. All of our requests were taken care of. Room service was on time and exactly as ordered. The coffee is great. I like that each department in this hotel asks what other kinds of services you need. For example, when you call room service at night for coffee the next day, they ask if you need a wake-up call. If you set up a wake-up call, they ask if you want room service for breakfast. Club Level: Club level cost about $200 extra per night during our trip. Because room service, hotel food, and drinks are quite costly, $200 for us to have access to the club lounge was well worth it. Brandon, the concierge, was absolutely incredible, as were Wanda and the rest of the club level staff. He took great care of us, and the personalized service was really nice. It's good to have a place right on the same floor as your room to get good coffee, read the paper, check email, and, of course, drink and snack at five daily food presentations. We met a lot of great people in the club lounge, too.The Beach and Pool: Well-manicured. The pool was clean. There were enough chairs and umbrellas to go around, and the staff take care of setting you up with chairs and towels. The beach was average--not perfectly white sand and clear water, but nice. They also have hammocks. We took a Hobie Cat ride (included in the resort fee) with their captain, and that was a lot of fun. They have bartenders that come around to get drink orders, plus staff that offer cold towels and small cups of lemon ice when it's hot out. I found the experience of hanging out by the pool and beach very relaxing and stress-free.The Spa: We did not get any treatments, but did use the indoor whirlpool and sauna, which were great. Other reviewers mentioned staff coming in and out of the area. We only saw one staffer come in to make sure we had what we needed and throw water on the coals. The locker-rooms are very clean, well-stocked with towels and toiletries, and the attendant is nice.The Gym: Small, crowded before dinnertime, but fine.The lobby: Fairly small and understated compared with the Vegas-style El San Juan nearby, but hopping on weekends with Latin music and dancing. Attentive bartenders. Drinks are steep--$14-$16 for mojitos. Casino: Typical of San Juan. Fairly small. Plenty of low-stakes machines and tables for gambling wimps like me.BLT Steak: Excellent food and service. The best bartenders anywhere. Check-out: Very easy.A note on the crazy mini-bar lady: A prior reviewer's comment that the mini-bar lady is obnoxious did ring true! She barged in immediately after knocking, and did this to another guest that we met. She did this to me after I told her less than an hour earlier that we did not need her services. Ask for a Do Not Disturb sign upon check-in. The staff will honor this the entire time and no one will knock; this is the best defense! (In case hotel staff read this, we actually met two mini-bar people. Only one was actually intrusive.)Other reviewers have commented that this property does not live up to the Ritz name. In terms of service, staff got it right and went above and beyond to make us happy. I can see how some might not feel the rooms are posh enough, but then the price for standard rooms ($239) was actually very reasonable. We'll stay here again. 
