<Content>Ritz ~ A++++ ~ 2 days stay after cruise Hi ~ We just returned from a 2 day stay at the Ritz following a cruise from San Juan. We had a GREAT experience with this resort. We have stayed at several Ritz's and found this to be one of our favorites. PROS: 1) Location - very close $10 trip to and from the airport. The don't have a shuttle, but taxi's are always waiting 2) Pool - Gorgeous as always - chairs so comfy - never a wait for the perfect spot. Pool staff always removed left towels, so finding the perfect spot was always easy. Tons of comfy water floats. Shorbet poolside, cool towels ~ all the great little Ritz perks. We booked Club Level. Our 1st time A++++++++++ - highly recommend - don't let the $100 per night run you off. You WILL get your $$ worth. Drinks, bottled water, wine, champagne - tons of food selections all throughout the day and night. Again, HIGHLY recommend. Free Internet. Great water activitites - also free (or should I say included in daily resort fee). Bottled waters waiting for you at the door when you arrive. Great casino. Cute little boutique shops right on site. Hotel laid out soooooooo conveniently, hardly any walking involved to navigate around. CONS: 1) Location - yes, this was also a PRO, however while you are in the pool you can't help but pay attention to the loud plane taking off. In the room YOU NEVER hear them and I am a very light sleeper. 2) Restaurant prices - again, typical for Ritz, but that is why we loved Club Level. 3) Bellman - not the most pleasant as we have found in the other resorts 4) check-in - took over 30 minutes from those waiting in the same line with problems w/ their bills checking out at the same time ............. Again, we had a super great time. You can't go wrong at this hotel. The small little cons, were just minor things. Ritz top class alllllllll the way!! .......... I can't get enough of my pleasure :) 
