<Author>georgeandsheryl
<Content>A first class experience My family (wife and 2 kids, 12 and 15) recently returned from a long weekend at the Ritz Carlton in San Juan. We arrived at 2PM and were told our room was not ready yet but was invited to have a complimentary lunch at their restaurant by the pool while we waited. The food was delicious and the service warm and friendly. After lunch we checked in to our standard room (two double beds with a view of the pool and partial view of the beach). The wall mounted flat screen tv was great, as were the Bulgari toiletries in the bathroom. Over the next couple of days we sampled the continental and buffet breakfasts (the buffet is easily the better value, though both are expensive, as expected). One day they set up a barbecue grill poolside and prepared hotdogs, hamburgers and chicken sandwiches to order. For a break on the wallet we breakfasted at Denny's just outside the property. We jetskied, parasailed and hobi catted on the water, all of which was terrific. The beach is really nice, water is beautiful and warm and the staff sets up chairs/umbrellas for you. Uniformly the staff is pleasant, friendly, knowledgable and are well trained. There is a high ratio of staff to guests so you are never in want for long and sometimes they seem to anticipate your needs before you do. In short, I highly recommend the resort and would stay again. 
