<Author>justhte4ofus
<Content>CAN"T WAIT TO GO BACK! We just returned from a week at the Ritz Carlton in San Juan, Puerto Rico and all I can say is that it was one of the most fabulous trips we have ever gone on.We went during the school break. My husband, myself and our 15 year old daughter and 10 year old son.. When we arrived there was some confusion with the room. Let me tell you that we were upset at first but then one of the managers, Carlos came over to us and was genuinely concerned and only wanted to make us happy. Eventually the problem was rectified and I have to say that he handled it incredibly professionally and made us feel like he actually cared.Next, we stayed on the club level. I don't think I can even begin to describe how incredible the cub level was. The staff on the club level just couldnt do enough to make us happy. Everything was my pleasure and the funny thing was I really felt like they meant it. Rita, Venus, Rey, Robert and Brandon, the manager would have gone to any length to please us and all the other guests on the club level. I seriously felt like royalty as did the other people who we met who were also staying on the club level. They were just unbelievably incredible and I must say it made the vacation even more enjoyable.When I booked this I noticed many people commenting or asking about the club level and for those who are curious I will elaborate a little bit on the club level. They had 4 food presentations per day. Breakfast, lunch, hors d'oueveres and deserts and after dinner drinks. The food was so delicious and presented so beautifully, the staff was so nice and the room was so nice with the outdoor balcony overlooking the pool and the beach that you could stay there for every meal if you wanted to.We had made dinner reservations before we left New York and everything changed when we got there. I can't even tell you how helpful the club lounge staff was. Every time I changed my mind they changed the reservation. It was unbelievable. And, every single request I made (and I made many) their response was always My Pleasure. I can't even begin to say how wonderful they were. The beach was absolutely beautiful. Never ever had an issue with getting a chair (or four) wherever we wanted them on the beach. The pool was a little bit harder but just harder to get a chair where you wanted it if you didnt come early in the morning but I NEVER had a problem getting chairs at the pool in fact one day I really wanted to be in the first row around the pool and the pool person actually moved chirs closer to eachother to make room for 3 chairs for me in the first row around the pool. Also, we never, ever had a problem getting anything at the pool or on the beach. There were always waiters and waitresses coming over to us. that was never an isue. Also, by the pool for the kids they made snow cones for no charge and always had cold bottles of water at the pool and at the beach and they weere free. Also, they would come around the beach and the pool and give you cold washcloths which I thought was very nice.The rooms were beautiful. The resort was beautiful immaculately maintained. The water sports on the beach were great, totally accessible and most of them were free. I could go on and on. It was a fabulous vacation, a fabulous, beautiful resort and the staff really set the Ritz Carlton apart from other resorts. If you go make sure to look for Carlos at the front desk, and Brandon, Rita, Rey, Venus, Robert and Brandon and the others (I just can't remember all their names) in the club room.We can't wait to return! 
