<Author>caryaf
<Content>Elegance, with a glitch or two!! This was our first real trip to Puerto Rico, and the Ritz Carlton was our choice based on prior excellent experiences at other Ritz Carlton's!Unfortunatley, rain for three days and cloudy weather on the fourth dampened our experience, but the one and a half glorious sunny days, of our five, were spectacular.Quite simply, the Ritz in San Juan is an elegant hotel with all the good things that implies! The grounds are spectacular -- like visiting a botanical garden. The pool is elegant, the beach is superbly maintained and spotless.There's a sense of graciousness and quiet throughout the hotel. The lobbies are superbly maintained, and all the staff is quick with a good morning! which quickly extends to the guests making things so very pleasant here!At the pool and beach areas there are more than a sufficient number of people to help you with chairs, towels, drinks, and so on. Each is friendly and eager to help.But this IS an expensive hotel! Our ocean view, balcony room was large and most comfortable. The bathroom almost larger than some hotel rooms I've stayed in. Beds are comfy and cozy, and there's a huge flat screen TV.All this was for a room rate over $750 per nite, with a 10% charge added on for accessories like beach towels, use of the gym, etc.It's pretty much impossible to eat for less than $25 per person for breakfast, and a simple lunch is in the $35 per person range. Dinner is even more. All this is without liquor.BUT: the food is superb, the service excellent and the prices are what you would pay in any similar restaurant outside the hotel.Some other small annoyances:Room service was slow, and breakfast took over an hour, althought they promised 20 minutes. The food arrived cold. We were scheduled to go off for a day of touring, so this was quite inconveninet. In response to our dissatisfaction, though, the $55 breakfast for two charge was removed from our account.While the people in the hotel are incredibly friendly and helpful, many of the systems in the hotel, such as the one designed for check in, failed them. We waited all afternoon to get our room, which was a disappointment as we had paid extra on our air fare to get to Puerto Rico early. A promised upgrade, for which we were paying an additional $150/nite (club level), never materialized.A few mechanical problems also cropped up, such as the door handles falling off the balcony door, and the airconditioning thermostat failing on the first day.BUT:Puerto Rico is WONDERFUL! A GREAT VACATION SPOT! The food was fabulous everywhere we went, and the people bend over backwards to help. It's a very friendly place! Old San Juan is fabulous to walk around in, and there's just so much of interest in other neighborhoods. 
