<Author>amirgold
<Content>Great place for families! This is my second trip to the Ritz and each year they impress me more. This time we went with our now 2 1/2 year old and our 8 month old. Here is a breakdown (I like to write, sorry):Room - We stayed in a Standard room which we were a bit worried about, but got an excellent corporate rate (I would ask for one when you book) for the room. The room was very nice with plenty of towels, flat screen tv, plenty of towels and drawer space. It was a bit smaller than I am used to but that becuase e got 2 double beds, one for us and one for our daughter plus a crib. We found out later that a King room has a pull out twin sofa and more room. They supplied us with a nice Crib at no charge. This really impressed me, the maid came in a knew we had a toddler, next thing I know we had bed gaurds set up. They store your empty luggage too.Pool - Nice pool and only 3 ft deep. I guess this is the only non kid friendly part since there is not shallow 1 ft area for kids, but it was fine since we broght a floatee. Staff always there to set up chairs. Get this, they have pack-n-plays that they will set up for you. Tons of rafts to lie on in the pool. Only other drawback, its a bit chilly when you get in but gets to be refreshing afterwards.Ocean - Probably the best part of the hotel. Clean, great sand, very warm. I didnt expect such a nice beach on the atlantic but it was great. I dont care what anyone says, Ritz has the best beach location in Isla Verde. Plus once again staff there to set up chairs with umbrellas, set you up with pack-n-plays, buckets and shovels, fruit. Plenty of boogie boards, sail boats too.Food - Food was eh. Breakfast buffet got a bit boring after a while, expecially for $25 a pop. Coffee was very weak (I like my Coffee) We ate a few nights at Masa which was also overpriced for the quality. Sushi was good though. Didnt try to gourmet places so cant comment.Casino - Was nice. Fri and Sat nights they have poker which was a good way to spend time. Get a comp. card if you go, I got $50 added to my bill when I left and trust me, i didnt spend that much money or time there.Staff/Service - Excellent! Everything was My pleasure. Had an issue with a food delivery, got $100 knocked off my bill. Went to breakfast and dinner with my daughter, had portable DVD players brought to us each time with Dora the Explorer, toy balloons..one night they brought her ice cream on the house. I asked for a to go box for breakfast and some water to go, I got a big bottle of Figi water and 2 containers to fill up for the day (one way to save money). They definetly made you and your children feel welcome and pampered. I expecially likle to nightly turn down service with chocolates and more free water.Resort - The nice part of it is that everything is right next to each other, within 2 minute walk you can get from your room to the pool then to the beach. Everything was very clean (I saw them cleaning at 4AM when my daughter woke and I had to roll her back to sleep). Hallways and lobby were always clean. BTW, all of the above amenities were free of charge although you pay a 10% resort fee for it but its nice not to have think about that :)Overall great experience, keep up the good work Ritz! I hope to be back for a 3rd next January. 
