<Author>a206439
<Content>The Ritz was Great !!! My wife, kids, (12 and 9), and I stayed at the Ritz from July 15-22. In short, if this isn't a 5 star hotel, I don't know what is. Let me get the negatives out of the way first, so I can focus on all the positives:-Location: It's near the airport, you will hear planes while outside and probably if you have a room not facing the pool or beach-Beach: The water isn't as blue as Cancun or Aruba, but you can't blame the Ritz for that, it's combed every day, but there's some seaweed in the water-Price: Food and drink is priced at a resort rate...expensive. Breakfast buffet $17 per person, lunch by the pool consistently cost $75 for 4, a Vodka tonic $9...this added up over a 7 day stay.Now the positives:-The Staff: In short, they are the nicest bunch of people, always trying to help make your stay a nice one, always doing extra to assist you-The room: House cleaning 2x a day, thorough, willing to leave extra waters and chocolates at turndown service-The concierge: Efficient, never steered us wrong, understood how to direct a family to the best possible dining and attractions-The pool: Clean, not crowded (even on a weekend with the hotel full)All the little details were great. Complimentary fresh squeezed orange juice in the lobby, water and fruit by the pool, refrigerated washcloths in the workout facility. This is a first class hotel. I walked thru the Intercontinental Hotel and cannot believe the Ritz is not rated higher than that place. A few other notes:-I was not charged a resort fee even though AAVacations said I was subject to one...this saved me at least $200-We ate every breakfast at a place called Piu Bello...it was a 5 minute walk from the hotel, excellent food, and very reasonably priced. They also served lunch (very good) and had GREAT Gellato. In short, I would go back to the Ritz, but probably for a long weekend or without the kids. As nice as the hotel was, it's really not geared to kids over the age of 5...but if you want to impress the wife with a long weekend away, this is the place in San Juan for sure. 
