<Content>Just Amazing I went there for a long vacation, two weeks, and it was just beautiful. I'd wake up, go down to the outdoor pool, have an attendant lay out a towel on a lounge chair in the shade, help myself to the lemon/orange water at the front and just relax. Some days I'd go to the beach, have a different attendant set up a chair and umbrella for me, and relax while the waves crashed onto the shore. Its so peaceful and quiet. At night I checked out the gym, and its amazing. Five of the ten eliptical trainers and treadmills have personal TVs on the front, and several weight training machines as well. The cleaning staff comes by your room twice, once in the morning to clean, and then again to give you any extra shampoo, water bottles, towels, and chocolates you might find a neccesity. At any given time, walking down the hallway is interrupted by Good Morning or Do you need anything? you call the front desk and you hear: Hello Mr./Mrs./Ms. ______, how can i make your stay more enjoyable tonight? Its within walking distance of a car rental place, so you can drive down to Old San Juan or the rainforest if you'd like, the stay as a whole was beautiful and enjoyable. 
