<Content>Excellent Service During The Week My wife and I stayed at the Ritz Carlton from Monday through Thursday and we were very impressed with the hotel and the excellent service. The grounds are beautiful and very clean. Each staff person greeted us with a smile and did their very best to deliver prompt, courteous service. I felt that we were treated like royalty throughout our visit. We had one problem at the beginning with a tub drain and it was fixed within three minutes of our call to the desk.Our experience might be different than other reviewers here because we did not stay on a weekend, when it is apparently much more crowded and prone to service lapses. During the week, the beach and pool area are not overcrowded and we could get chairs and towels whenever we wanted. The concierge was extremely helpful whenever I had a question.We ate at the Prime 787 Restaurant and it was a wonderful meal. We also ate at the Lobby Bar, Poolside restaurant, and indoor Grill. On all occasions, the food was very good and the service was excellent. Meals are certainly not cheap(this is the Ritz after all), but not wildly expensive when compared to what you pay at many resort areas.Complimentary coffee is served in the lobby in the morning. If you don't want to pay for the breakfast buffet, you can go outside to the Dennys or other local shop down the street from Dennys.As most people have pointed out, the area right outside the hotel is not very nice at all. But I can't hold that against the hotel. Although planes are taking off and landing frequently, the noise was not loud and didn't bother us at all.The hotel also allows you to use the PC computer in the Business Center at no charge and they didn't charge for local or 800 access phone calls as some hotels do.Our experience at the hotel itself was first class all the way. 
