<Content>Fabulous Hotel...Wish I could live in the lap of luxury at the Ritz every day! 3 of my girlfriends and I stayed at the Ritz a few months ago for our 25th birthdays/bachelorette party. We booked our trip through Orbitz and got an extremely reasonable rate(~$280 a night)...not bad for a 5-star hotel! I must say that from the moment we walked in the door we were treated like princesses!!! Upon checking-in, the gentleman at the front desk overheard us telling some other hotel patrons that we were in Puerto Rico to celebrate our birthdays and promptly ordered 4 glasses of complimentary champagne for us! Furthermore, he upgraded us to a King-Size delux room for free!!! The bellhop also heard it was our birthdays and took us to the Club lounge were we were offered endless glasses of champagne, hors d'oeuvres, cookies, etc. It was quite a nice welcoming to say the least!By the end of the trip, word had spread amongst the hotel staff that we were celebrating our birthdays...the entire time we were there we were showered with complimentary drinks, desserts, etc. The staff at the lobby lounge even had a mini party for us!!! Needless to say, the staff at the Ritz went above and beyond their call of duty and truly made this a memorable trip. Contrary to some of the other reviews, I found the concierge desk extremely helpful. There was a food festival going on in Old San Juan the weekend we were there and therefore, many of the top restaurants were booked. The girls at the concierge desk, however, were able to get us reservations at Dragonfly (highly recommended Asian-Latino fusion food) and Tantra (great drinks, even better looking bartenders) with ease. In addition, the girl at the concierge desk gave us complimentary VIP passes to the club at the Wyndam down the street (apparently one of the hottest clubs in San Juan) which allowed us to skip the long lines and get in for free.We didn't eat dinner at any of the restaurants at the hotel, though did have breakfast/lunch at the pool nearly everyday. Service was great, food was what you'd expect from a poolside grill, and the drinks were so-so (though most of the time, we just drank the bottled water that was provided). Take advantage of the non-motorized activities...we didn't have an opportunity to take the catamarans or the kayaks out because the water was too choppy, but we wish we did! Overall, an amazing trip. The hotel is absolutely beautiful...everything is meticulously designed and cared for...from the lobby area, to the pool, and even the monstrous bathrooms (extremely useful for 4 girls trying to get ready in one room)! I certainly look forward to returning to this hotel! 
