<Content>A Great Quick Vacation! My husband and two children (aged 15 and 11) stayed at the Ritz-Carlton San Juan for 4 1/2 days in Febuary. It was a quick trip, but the Ritz is a perfect place to stay for a few days in the sun.For starters, the service at this hotel is spectacular, which we have often found to be rare in the islands where most things are done on island time. We received anything and everything asked for, and most of our requests were followed up by a phone call asking if everything had been taken care of satisfactorily. The only area that needs some help is the concierge desk. I was put on terminal hold a number of times when I called, and not once did they call me back with the information I was looking for. Basically I just had to leave the beach and go to the desk and get the attention of someone to help me if I wanted anything done or questions answered. This area is sorely overworked and service is lacking.Otherwise, our hotel rooms were very comfortable and quiet....ours had a fantastic view of the pool and beach (definitely worth it as the rooms on the back of the hotel face the runway of the airport). The beach and pool are lovely, although the pool can be a bit cramped, but there are chairs for all who want one. The beach is beautiful, although you do hear the planes arriving and taking off from the nearby airport which could be a problem for those looking for total peace and quiet. No problem for us. The service is good at both the pool and beach (better when these areas are not too crowded). We ate lunch on the beach or at the pool which was very convenient (good, quick food although expensive for what you get). The exercise classes (lots of them all day long) and the exercise room are great and the spa is wonderful. We played tennis a couple of days and the courts are adequate but the tennis clinic (lessons) are not really worth it. You need to stay somewhere else for better athletic facilities if you plan on playing lots of tennis or golf. This is really a city property and they are limited to a small amount of space.We only ate dinner at the hotel steak house, Prime 787, which was delicious and the service was very good. We also ate at 2 other restaurants that I can recommend, Pamelas in San Juan on the beach and at Dragonfly in OSJ....quite a scene with fantastic food. Loved them both. I think the Ritz should have a place to just pick up coffee and a bagel for breakfast (something for on the go....) but rather they only have a place to sit down and eat a full breakfast. All in all, this is a fantastic hotel for a quick trip for some warm weather and sun. I would not stay here for an extended vacation, but I would surely go back for another quick one. 
