<Content>Wonderful Attentive Staff...Above Average Property My husband and I stayed at the property August 27th and 28th and had a delightful stay! The drive from the airport is only 5 minutes and you can see the property from the plane. The check in was quick and they had iced towels and fresh juice available. As it was my Birthday, they gave us a complimentary upgrade to a junior suite, which faced another building, but the ocean could be still seen.The rooms are showing some signs of wear. Our drapes, carpet and throw pillows had stains on them, but all of the amenities and comforts are available, including generous sizes of Bulgari bath amenities. Despite being so close to the airport, the rooms are soundproofed and we slept well on the comfortable featherbed.We had lunch in the Caribbean Grill. The services was a bit slow, but our food was hot and delicious and the staff gracious. We did the tour with Here and There of the Bacardi Factory (recommended) and old San Juan and our driver was very personable and almost like family as he guided us around and even stopped at Cafe Puerto Rico after a group consensus was reached for authentic cuisine. This was not part of the tour and we ended up having the tour extended for one hour at no additional cost. The concierge can arrange the tour ($40) for 5 hours...ours was 6 hours.We had dinner at Prime 787. The meal was pricey, however the service was attentive and on point. The food is similar to a Ruth Chris or a Mortens. The staff brought out a complimentary plate of chocolates that had Happy Birthday written in chocolate for me and they gave me a card that was signed by the staff. The concierge also gave the restaurant staff a gift to deliver to me with a card and lotion and body wash. Very thoughtful and much appreciated!The casino was fair. There definitely appeared to be a mix of locals and guests of the Ritz and other hotels. There is a good variety of games available.The beach, pool areas and gym are clean and adequately staffed. We had absolutely no problem finding chairs at the pool with umbrellas during peak hours. Waiters come by frequently if you need drinks, food, etc.Upon check out, we had a small problem with our bill with something that was not deducted, but they rectified it and showed us their in house system and printed out a correct bill.I have no complaints of this hotel other than it could use some interior upgrades. I would definitely stay here again. 
