<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>loved it I was nervous about going to Puerto Rico after reading some of the reviews, but like anywhere else in this world you just need to be alert. My boyfriend and I stayed at the Ritz Carlton the week of June 15th. I loved this hotel. The rooms were very comfortable, with all the little touches you would expect from a Ritz Hotel. The staff was well trained and we had no problems. The bed was very comfortable - we booked a room with pool/ocean view. The bathroom is large with lots of marble. What did upset me was that we had to wait to check in until 3pm, the room was not ready until then and we arrived around noon. They offer you the opportunity to change and hold your bags if you don't want to wait to get on the beach. I liked the beach, it was never really crowded and it did seem that a few locals went there on the weekend. The pool was beautiful, it was never really packed even on the weekend. We never had to stake a claim on a lounge, there were always plenty and very comfortable like mini-beds. There were as many towels as u needed, and the staff came around for drink orders on a pretty daily basis/ bringing chilled towels, etc. The hotel is very pretty and to me is the perfect location because its close to town. When we visited old san juan, there are a lots of places to walk around, drink and eat. The night we went in for dinner/drinks there was a definite police presence, it seems they make their rounds often in the areas that are filled with tourists. Everyone we encountered was very nice and friendly. Every restaurant we ate in was good. I would recommend Ruth Chris's, The Parrott Club and there is also an intalian place in san juan right by the main square that the cab drivers seem to bring everyone. The Metrople was very good cuban food, and its very reasonable, casual place. Its right up the street from the hotel. The Caribbean Grill for breakfast was good, a little pricey though. Restaurant out by pool on the beach was good too for lunch/drinks. Most of the reviews I read on this site were pretty accurate as far as restaurants. We discovered on our last night a lot of nice restaurants/clubs/shops - an overall nice area by the Wyndham Condado. We had dinner in an italian restaurant there that overlooked the ocean, a cute place. It seems they are really building that area up and I wish we had found it sooner. Dont be afaid to rent a car and go on your own, we took a trip to the el yunque rain forest and then to loquillo beach. Its pretty, more tropical and rougher water than the ritz beach. it was no problem to get around. I would definitely recommend the Ritz for their location, its very pretty and well maintained, the pool is beautiful and the beach was nice too. The staff were all nice also. If we went back i wouldnt hesitate to go there again. Yes you can hear the planes since its near the airport but it really doesnt happen enough to be annoying. Even though youre still in the U.S., it definitely felt like youre really away, and with such a short flight its worth it. The temperatures were very high the week we went, (record highs) so if you're planning to go into town to see El Morro go super early. The views were pretty but it was way too hot. The Ritz we felt was the best choice in that area and worth the money. 
