<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Wonderful Hotel - Worth the Price I'm a business traveler who travels fairly frequently (10-20 trips per year), and I have stayed in a wide variety of hotels. The Ritz in San Juan is definitely among the top hotels I have stayed at. First, the pros and cons:Pros:1. Spectacular pool, open 24 hours a day2. Incredibly attentive staff. Anything I needed was immediately provided3. Beautiful, well-groomed beach4. Good security in hotel and on grounds5. Wide selection of restaurants within walking distance6. Top-notch room with comfortable bed, great bathroom7. Free high-speed internet access8. Stunningly beautiful facility and grounds9. Decent, if uninspiring casinoCons:1. Very close to the airport; so close you can hear the planes and smell the jet fuel (Can't hear the jets in the room, tho)2. My corridor smelled oddly like cat urine (believe it or not)3. $15- $20 each way cab ride from business district4. Very expensive parking5. No coffee maker in roomOverall, this was a very pleasant experience. This is definitely a quality hotel; you can see that from the courteous and numerous bellhops at the front door, to the detail-oriented and attentive staff behind the check-in desks, to the top-quality/high-thread count linens in the spotlessly clean room.The hotel restaurants (as most are) are very expensive ($15 for a hamburger, and $15 for a continental breakfast). However, numerous other options are readily available. I usually ate dinner at a wonderful local establishment calld 'Ediths' (I believe). It was about a 5 minute walk from the hotel. As you exit the hotel's front door and reach the street, turn right...there are at least 5 reasonable restaurants within a 5 minute walk, as well as a well-stocked pharmacy. Ediths (in particular) had wonderful Cubanos, as well as many Puerto Rican specialties, most for well under $10. They also had $2 Coronas that you could take with you.The hotel grounds are immaculate and beautiful. Plenty of flowers, fountains, and birds. The pool was amazing. Large and temperate, it is open 24 hours, with big fluffy towels availabe at the cabana immediately next to it. There is also a nice jacuzzi in the poor area that looks out onto the beach.The beach itself was very well cared for, and in the evenings is watched over by security (we had a security gurd named Matos who was excellent, friendly and helpful...great staff all around). The ocean water is rather silty, but fine for swimming.The room was a 5-star quality room. King size bed, with great sheets and pillows, large well-equipped bathroom. The only odd lapse was that the maid forgot to give us washcloths on 2 of the days we were there. High-speed internet access is free and convenient (Take a note Hilton - If I can choose between a Hilton and the Ritz, the fact that the internet is free at the Ritz WILL make a difference to me).For some odd reason, the hallway outside my room consistently smelled like cat urine. It wasn't overwhelming, just disquieting and surprising. But that was about the only negative.Overall, this was among the nicest hotels I have ever stayed at. I got a good corporate rate, and it was worth more than what I paid. I will stay here again; it is most assuredly a 5-star hotel, with a Puerto Rican touch. I don't think you will be disappointed if you stay here. 
