<Content>We loved it!!! MY husband and i were married in Sept of 2002 and we stayed at the Ritz Carlton and we absolutely loved it!!! When we arrived the door men were polite and very attentive, and the overall atmosphere was just beautiful and very pleasant!I am actually a little upset with some of the reviews from the other guest. My husband and i had such a wonderful time! I suppose the time of year you go to visit has a lot to do with it. We went in Sept which meant kids were back in school, and all the summer vacationers were back to work. I honestly loved my stay and would recommend it to anyone!!The beach was private and very clean! wasn't over crowded and we weren't bothered by anyone! Some nights we actually went out on the beach at very late hours of the night and there was always a security guard on stand by patrolling. My hubby and i actually conceived our first child on our honey in PR! To us that said a lot!! Definitely a place for the mature, and the more laid back. My hubby and i were actually in our early 20's when we took our trip and it was just our speed. If we wanted to party and act crazy we would have gone to Cancun or some other place. But Ritz Carlton in PR was very relaxing and just wonderful!To my hubby and i... everything was just great!! The food, the room(which had a balcony and a wonderful view of the court yard where the pool was), room service, house keeping, the casino..EVERYTHING!! The floor we stayed on was a private floor. The only way to this floor was to use your room key on the elevator... this floor had a beautiful concierge lounge that had wonderful food and as many drinks(fountain as well as alcoholic beverage) at no price. This was also a highlight of our stay because we could fill ourselves up with the goodies from the lounge and be alright until lunch, or dinner. The lounge hours were great and the hosts and hostesses were very polite and very attentive. The view was also gorgeous from the balcony too!Oh and one thing we absolutely loved, was that we never had to wonder how we would get around. There was always a taxi ready and willing to take you anywhere you needed to go and it was normally a very good price!The Ritz Carlton is the place to go if you ask me!!My hubby and i will be going back hopefully in a few weeks and we can't wait!! 
