<Author>mhpw
<Content>Perfect relaxation Myhusband and I spent five nights at the Ritz Carlton San Juan in early April. We were aiming for pure relaxation and rejuvenation, and we have no doubt that we made the right hotel selection. The rooms were great. They were not huge, but not as small as some of the reviews make them sound. There was plenty of room for a large comfortable chair, a desk, a tv cabinet, and a dresser, with room left over. The bed was very comfortable (the down matress pad made us feel as if we were sleeping on a cloud). The bathroom was very spacious and quite nice (marble counter, lighted makeup/shaving mirror, a seperate room for the toilet, etc.). Finally, the rooms were perfectly clean, and the housekeeping service (twice daily) was great.The restaurants at the resort were fine, although it is definitely worth taking a cab to Old San Juan for dinners, as there are some exceptional restaurants there (Dragonfly, Baru, etc.). Tangerine at the Water Club hotel is also a great dinner choice. But we did have dinner at the Ritz steakhouse one night, which was delicious even though the portions were quite small, and we ate breakfast every morning on the outside patio of the main hotel restaurant, which was very pleasant and not too expensive.The pool area was very nice, and surrounded by beautiful lush gardens. The chairs surrounding the pool were very comfortable -- be prepared to drift off! There are a lot of kids around the pool, but we did not find them to be annoying at all, and in fact found it pleasant and amusing to watch them swim and play. The staff makes frequent rounds to ask if you would like a drink, or to give you free frozen watermelon or offer a cold washcloth (this was true on the beach as well).The beach was nice, and very clean. I am not sure what reviewers who say the beach is dirty saw, but we saw no evidence of this at all. The only complaint that we had about the beach was that although there are stands for six hammocks, four were broken -- so there are only two working hammocks on the beach. No big deal, though -- they weren't in too high a demand, and we were able to use them several times.The casino was a lot of fun. Although we are not frequent or high stakes gamblers, my husband had a great time playing Blackjack, and I spent a few hours on the slots over the week and -- in the end -- only came up 5 cents short. It is definitely worth it to go have some fun in the casino, as the waitresses walk around taking orders for free drinks, so even if you loose a little money, you probably still come out ahead with the money you might have otherwise spent on drinks!We also spent a lot of time sitting on the patios just outside the main building, enjoying drinks and reading and doing crosswords, etc. The waitresses from the lobby bar will come out and wait on you out there. That was a very relaxing way to pass time!Finally, I did use the spa for one treatment, and it was great. The spa has a very nice atmosphere, and it is worth using even if you are not getting a treatment (they have a sauna  steamroom, etc.).Although no vacation is so perfect that you can't find things to complain about it you really try, you will really enjoy your time at the Ritz Carlton if you go in with a good attitude and do your best to relax and just enjoy your time in Puerto Rico! 
