<Content>5 Star Wow! First time to Puerto Rico and the first time staying at the Ritz. This is truly luxury at it's finest. The staff is amazing, the accomodations are the best. Upon check in we were upgraded to the Club level floors that have their own conceirge host as well as access to continental breakfast, mid afternoon snack, tea, and cocktail hour in the evening.The rooms were spacious, the bed, pillows (which we bought), robes, the bathroom were amazing. The pool area was fantastic and beautiful at night as well. They also serve lunch/drinks by the pool. The beach was very nice too. They'll personally escort you to your lounge chair and get you all set up for a day in the sun. The spa treatments were amazing. It may cost you a small fortune but aren't you worth it! Made a donation to the Casino in the hotel. Nice casino, a bunch of slots, but a small number of tables.Ate at one of the hotel restaurants, Carribean Grill, for lunch. It was ok and the cost was silly. lunch for two was $60, I had a burger and wife had a salad. Two great restaurants to go to in San Juan are Pikayo (in the musuem of art). It is amazing, i compare it to Jean George in NYC. The other is Tangerine in the Waterclub Hotel. A Miami Beach like scene. Servings are small but tasty and the nightclub/bar scene at the top of the hotel is great.Hotel is within 10 minute walking distance to the El San Juan and the Intercontinental Hotels. And it's only a 5 minute cab ride from the airport. All in all, I plan a return trip to San Juan and I'm definetly staying at the Ritz. 
