<Content>Outstanding Service and Quality We arrived at the Ritz for a 4 night vacation begining on Nov 3. The hotel itself is first class all the way. Everything is perfectly manicured. The staff is the most responsive I've ever seen and I have been on a lot of vacations. The complaints I've read about being close to the airport just aren't accurate. While in the hotel, you never know you are close. Out at the beach you sometimes hear the planes on the runway but the kids love watching them take off in the distance. Yes, if you are out front of the hotel it's loud when they take off. I would love to see it be a bit more kid friendly but it wasn't obnoxious either. A water slide or swim up bar would make it a bit more interesting at the pool. The casino is first rate and clean, not like the El San Juan up the road which seems to be a local hangout for everyone and is a bit run down around the edges. Sure, it's a party place with lots of beautiful young people if you are going to party....but if you want top class service with your family, stay at the Ritz instead. The level of service and comfort at the Ritz can't be matched by anything in that area of the island. The sand on the beach at the Ritz is literally like walking on powder. It's so soft and smooth. Completely clean. 
