<Content>We loved the Ritz and would definitely return! My husband, 17 mo daughter and I arrived at the Ritz on Friday during the Memorial Day weekend and stayed Club Level (9th floor). Check-in was quick - no complaints. The room was a bit small but well appointed. We had asked to have the room POLO'd (protect our little ones - Ritz' childproofing) and it was not done. The crib we had ordered arrived shortly after we got there. The service on a whole was great. Everyone seemed to go out of their way to be friendly and helpful. As someone else mentioned, if you asked where something was, the staff would walk you to it. Housekeeping was OK. There was a bit of a language barrier at some points. But otherwise, the room was always cleaned while we were out. We were never inconvenienced by their presence.The Club lounge was definitely worth it and I would strongly recommend it to others. There was always plenty of food and lots of variety. The lounge staff was very accommodating and always aimed to please. One day we decided to have afternoon tea (done upon request) and, although we had to wait a bit, it was definitely worth it. The one complaint I have with the lounge is that some of the patrons did not observe the rules of etiquette nor the dress code. The staff rarely mentioned the rules to those persons...The pool area was very nice and it didn't get too crowded. It is true that in order to get a good beach chair location, you need to arrive by the pool no later than 9. We only ate once by the pool and the food was OK. The beach area was nice as well. I did not see many non-Ritz guests by the beach. There was always plenty of beach chairs available.We had the seafood buffet (on Friday nights at the Caribbean Grill) and it was fantastic. Worth the $49 pp. Our meal at the Vineyard Grill was outstanding and the service superb.The proximity to the airport was nice and the noise of the jets was not too bothersome. After the first few times, you hardly noticed it. All in a